    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \langle \mathbf {p} _{k},\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle &lt;0}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9894268782f52f9062310818ea1666a9473f8e69" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.202ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \langle \mathbf {p} _{k},\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle &lt;0}"></span>, where <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \langle ,\rangle }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- ⟨ --></mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- ⟩ --></mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \langle ,\rangle }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/528cb832a8e8af1633a9396fef5bb588f563395b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:2.843ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \langle ,\rangle }"></span> denotes the <a href="/wiki/Inner_product" class="mw-redirect" title="Inner product">inner product</a>. The motivation for such an approach is that small steps along <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \mathbf {p} _{k}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">p</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {p} _{k}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/06b38cae31fcc9a4db19b6ac10e053f708135b9c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:2.574ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \mathbf {p} _{k}}"></span> guarantee that <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
          <mi>f</mi>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \displaystyle f}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/07d97d49d29cc57cce35ed58129778c7bb0d8501" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.279ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f}"></span> is reduced, by <a href="/wiki/Taylor%27s_theorem" title="Taylor&#39;s theorem">Taylor's theorem</a>.
</p><p>Using this definition, the negative of a non-zero gradient is always a
descent direction, as <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \langle -\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k}),\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle =-\langle \nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k}),\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle &lt;0}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- ⟨ --></mo>
        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- − --></mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- ∇ --></mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- ∇ --></mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- ⟩ --></mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- − --></mo>
        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- ⟨ --></mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- ∇ --></mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- ∇ --></mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant="bold">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- ⟩ --></mo>
        <mo>&lt;</mo>
        <mn>0</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \langle -\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k}),\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle =-\langle \nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k}),\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle &lt;0}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/394cefd504d4817fe405f946e605bba19f16a325" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:46.756ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \langle -\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k}),\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle =-\langle \nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k}),\nabla f(\mathbf {x} _{k})\rangle &lt;0}"></span>.
</p><p>Numerous methods exist to compute descent directions, all with differing merits, such as <a href="/wiki/Gradient_descent" title="Gradient descent">gradient descent</a> or the <a href="/wiki/Conjugate_gradient_method" title="Conjugate gradient method">conjugate gradient method</a>.
</p><p>More generally, if <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle P}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>P</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle P}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b4dc73bf40314945ff376bd363916a738548d40a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.745ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle P}"></span> is a <a href="/wiki/Positive_definite" class="mw-redirect" title="Positive definite">positive definite</a> matrix, then
<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle p_{k}=-P\nabla f(x_{k})}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>p</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- − --></mo>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2207;<!-- ∇ --></mi>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle p_{k}=-P\nabla f(x_{k})}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b203f8151d41a3152e9582b32197a8bd84a62f19" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:16.442ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle p_{k}=-P\nabla f(x_{k})}"></span> is a descent direction at <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle x_{k}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle x_{k}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6d2b88c64c76a03611549fb9b4cf4ed060b56002" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.418ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle x_{k}}"></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-?_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-?-1"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>1<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> This generality is used in <a href="/wiki/Preconditioned_gradient_descent" class="mw-redirect" title="Preconditioned gradient descent">preconditioned gradient descent</a> methods.
</p>
